HEADWORD: Concludent
<hw>Con*clud"ent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>concludens</ets>, p. pr.]</ety> <def>Bringing to a close; decisive;
conclusive.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Arguments highly consequential and <qex>concludent</qex> to my
purpose.</q> <rj><qau>Sir M. Hale.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Concluder</ent>⟦br⟧
